==Spanish==
===Etymology===
From the older ''[[pássaro]]''

===Noun===
'''pájaro''' ''m'' 

#[[bird]], [[fowl]]

====Synonyms====
*[[ave]]

====Derived terms====
*[[espantapájaros]] {{m}}
*[[pájaro cantor]]: [[songbird]]
*[[pájaro bobo]] (or [[pingüino]]): [[penguin]]
*[[pájaro carpintero]]: [[woodpecker]]

====Proverbs====
* '''No hay pájaros en los nidos de ayer.''' 
Literally: ''There are no birds in the nests of yesterday''. Meaning: Youth passes quickly.
* '''Más vale pájaro en mano que ciento volando'''
Literally: ''(One) bird in the hand is worthier than a hundred flying''. Meaning: A bird in the hand is worth two in the bush.
